{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_140","type":"agent_message","text":"# Implementation Notes\n\n## Decisions Made\n- Added `FlowSemantics` and `stage_plan_for_flow(...)` in [mod.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs) so built-in flows map structural roles instead of hardcoded standard-stage IDs.\n- Generalized the orchestration engine in [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs) to `execute_run` / `resume_run`, preserved `execute_standard_run` / `resume_standard_run` as wrappers, and switched remediation, completion-round restart, amendment drain, prompt-review pause, and resume reconstruction to flow-semantics lookups.\n- Updated CLI handling in [run.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs) so `docs_change` and `ci_improvement` run on the shared engine while `quick_dev` still returns `UnsupportedFlow`.\n- Added coverage in [workflow_engine_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs), [flow_semantics_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/flow_semantics_test.rs), [cli.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs), and the new feature files [run_start_docs_change.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_docs_change.feature), [run_start_ci_improvement.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_ci_improvement.feature), and [run_resume_non_standard.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_resume_non_standard.feature). I also corrected the outdated docs/CI support text in [run_start_standard.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature).\n\n## Spec Deviations\n- Non-late `ConditionallyApproved` outcomes still do not persist follow-ups in `run.json`. The current canonical model only has the durable amendment queue, and the spec also says docs/CI flows should not queue durable amendments, so I preserved the existing non-blocking behavior instead of inventing a new snapshot field in this loop.\n\n## Testing\n- Verified with `cargo test` and fixed the only failing case uncovered during the run. Because this shell did not expose `cargo` or `cc` on `PATH`, I ran the suite with explicit Nix toolchain/linker paths.\n\n---"}}
